<font color="blue"><b>:::: Kamasutra drinks a flask of fermented Paladin Eye Wisky.. Glug, glug, glug, glug. Ahhhh! That was refreshing! ::::</font></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udeo.showPublicProfile>Deo</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/TimesSquare/Alley/6046/rogueicon.jpg BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/25/00 4:32:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscouncildiscussions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Etiquette</span><hr size=1> Nobody said it was &quot;law&quot;. I'm not saying it is a law or legally enforceable by anyone. The POINT I'm trying to make is that so far, NOBODY has discussed any issues that can be furthered here. Enlightenment.<br>
<br>
We don't need a council to just start events that are already occurring. Events between guilds can also be addressed here or between the guilds themselves. If you think that I'm proposing rules, you're wrong.<br>
<br>
A point I disagree with you strongly is that we all maturely try to solve things. People have different ideas of what mature is. Also, between cultures, there are different ideas of how such things are taken care of. If anything, never ASSUME that everyone is on the same page. It's much better to have a discussion about this to see how everyone feels about an issue. The issue I put up as example is one of them. Some might feel that involving guild officers is inappropriate, while others might always involve guild officers. There are many more different situations, but there should be a common understanding. If we don't TALK about it here, then some people may think guildwar is the only way of solving something that started between two individuals over something stupid.<br>
<br>
Once again, the emphasis is on *communication*. THIS is communication. I don't think hammering out ideas on procedures is LAW because I haven't mentioned punishments or consequences. I have just proposed in my example ideas on how to AGREE on issues. If you think that we all think the same thing, then you are wrong. If you disagree with my hypothetical list, then that is prime example of the need to have an open discussion about what is commonly accepted or not. Sure, you don't have to do anything you don't want to, but I'm flexible enough to go through a process because it is a common ground.<br>
<br>
This type of disagreement was common during the birth of the United States as some favored a Confederacy vs Federal government. Just pointing out without a common language to go with, we won't get anywhere on communication. If there are other issues regarding our server, so be it. I'm open to anything, but it's a lot better than all talking about solving problems and not actually working to fix them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(2/25/00 11:58:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildscouncildiscussions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Etiquette</span><hr size=1> A good beginning to the discussion, Deodrid. I'm glad you qualified your first statements by saying these suggestions would not be law. <br>
<br>
I would agree we should discuss some options here. We all have to deal with each other when one of our members is accused of killstealing. We all must decide where our individual guilds stand on such issues. Our charters are meant to tell our members what we think about such actions. <br>
<br>
But what does the council think? What are some of the issues we need to discuss?<br>
<br>
Are there any guilds where kill-stealing is NOT frowned upon? <br>
What guilds exist purely for roleplay and purely for fun? And do most of us fall in the middle somewhere? <br>
<br>
As guild leaders, how much or how little control should we/do we exert over our guilds?<br>
<br>
Ok, people, let's get to talking here.<br>
<br>
